<p>Safety advisers in Birmingham and West Midlands Police barred Maccabi Tel Aviv supporters from attending a Europa League match at Aston Villa due to public safety risks [dw.com#1][aljazeera.com#1][politico.eu#1]. Police said the decision was based on current intelligence and previous violent incidents, referencing clashes involving Maccabi Tel Aviv and Ajax fans in Amsterdam last year [politico.eu#1]. UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer called the move “wrong,” arguing police should ensure all fans can attend safely, while Israel’s foreign minister Gideon Sa’ar labeled it “shameful” [politico.eu#1][ft.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. UEFA said that safety and security decisions for matches are the responsibility of competent local authorities in the host country [politico.eu#1][aljazeera.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/-gNopLoFXynm9xKCrk4BSFkIzRs-kOY6bxO-w1NVJ1YMCulfAZ0C1Mv1JnFbYKyw_fFElWhA3czW6pDGImpnWMu4vngsQOE2x2pwyY5DwnS5PHEbN2RqIVB_fQzvUkXYGlbIsYEqZjsHbuiKQFRugdzQZ1dA66Iz3uDclv6GfOXP8dKrjfL16tW28sVB0Dpl84JqQbqawT_9TxXRmw' alt='Europa League fixture preparations as the UK reviews away-fan attendance.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Government review: Senior UK officials are meeting to consider reversing the decision, with the culture secretary consulting the Home Office after a minister called the ban “completely and utterly unacceptable” [theguardian.com#2].</li><li>Oversight check: The West Midlands police and crime commissioner requested a review to assess whether the ban is appropriate, necessary, justified and reasonable [theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Amsterdam context: After two days of unrest in Amsterdam last year, five people were hospitalized and more than 60 arrests were made, which officials described as a “toxic combination” of factors [politico.eu#1].</li><li>Hate-crime stance: West Midlands Police reaffirmed a zero‑tolerance policy on hate crime and expressed support for affected communities in their statement [politico.eu#1].</li><li>Scope of ban: Only away supporters — Israeli fans — are barred from attending at Villa Park; home attendance is unaffected [dw.com#1][thehindu.com#1][aljazeera.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>We will not tolerate antisemitism on our streets. - Keir Starmer</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Keir Starmer: Called the decision wrong and said police should ensure all fans can enjoy the game without fear. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/keir-starmer-slams-decision-to-ban-maccabi-tel-aviv-football-fans-from-uk-match/'>POLITICO Europe</a>)</li><li>West Midlands Police: Said the measure is based on intelligence and prior incidents and will mitigate risks to public safety, while maintaining zero tolerance on hate crime. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/keir-starmer-slams-decision-to-ban-maccabi-tel-aviv-football-fans-from-uk-match/'>POLITICO Europe</a>)</li><li>Israel’s Foreign Ministry: Foreign Minister Gideon Sa’ar condemned the move as “shameful.”. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/keir-starmer-slams-decision-to-ban-maccabi-tel-aviv-football-fans-from-uk-match/'>POLITICO Europe</a>)</li><li>UEFA: Emphasized that competent local authorities are responsible for safety and security decisions at host venues. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/keir-starmer-slams-decision-to-ban-maccabi-tel-aviv-football-fans-from-uk-match/'>POLITICO Europe</a>)</li><li>UK Department for Culture, Media and Sport: A minister called the ban “completely and utterly unacceptable,” with the culture secretary set to discuss the issue with the Home Office. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2025/oct/17/government-officials-seek-lift-ban-maccabi-tel-aviv-fans-aston-villa-game'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>West Midlands Police and Crime Commissioner: Requested a review to determine if the ban is appropriate, necessary, justified and reasonable. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/politics/live/2025/oct/17/keir-starmer-uk-politics-latest-news-updates-maccabi-tel-aviv-fans-banned'>The Guardian</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/football-maccabi-tel-aviv-fans-banned-from-aston-villa-game/a-74393364'>Football: Maccabi Tel Aviv fans banned from Aston Villa game</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/sport/football/israeli-clubs-fans-banned-from-attending-europa-league-match-at-aston-villa-pm-starmer-slams-decision/article70174506.ece'>Israeli club’s fans banned from attending Europa League match at Aston Villa; PM Starmer slams decision</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/keir-starmer-slams-decision-to-ban-maccabi-tel-aviv-football-fans-from-uk-match/'>Keir Starmer slams decision to ban Maccabi Tel Aviv fans from UK match</a> - politico.eu</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/17/israeli-maccabi-tel-aviv-football-fans-barred-from-europa-league-game-in-uk'>Israeli Maccabi Tel Aviv football fans barred from Europa League game in UK</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/politics/live/2025/oct/17/keir-starmer-uk-politics-latest-news-updates-maccabi-tel-aviv-fans-banned'>Police commissioner calls for review of Maccabi Tel Aviv fans’ ban from UK match after PM’s criticism – politics live</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/4df9a131-312f-4eef-93ef-5e6ebf244b26'>Starmer condemns decision to ban Maccabi Tel Aviv fans from Aston Villa game</a> - ft.com</li></ul>